@startuml

title Private Vocabulary Flashcard Domain Schema

class Vocabulary {
  +id : VocabularyId
  +userId : UserId
  +surface : String
  +translation : String
  +entryKind : EntryKind
  +notes : String?
  +exampleSentences : List<VocabularyExampleSentence>
}

class VocabularyId {
  +id : String
}

class UserId {
  +id : String
}

class VocabularyExampleSentence {
  +id : VocabularyExampleSentenceId
  +sentence : String
  +translation : String
}

class VocabularyExampleSentenceId {
  +id : String
}

class FlashCardReview {
  +id : FlashCardId
  +userId : UserId
  +contentId : ContentId
  +isReversed : boolean
  +cardReviewData : FsrsCardState
}

class VocabularyFlashCardData {
  +id : FlashCardId
  +frontWordOrChunk : String
  +backWordOrChunk : String
  +sentences : List<SentenceData>
  +isReversed : boolean
}

class SentenceData {
  +id : String
  +sentence : String
  +translation : String
}

class FsrsCardState {
  +json : String
}

class FlashCardId {
  +id : String
}

class ContentId {
  +id : String
}

Vocabulary --> VocabularyId
Vocabulary --> UserId
Vocabulary *-- "1..*" VocabularyExampleSentence : exampleSentences
VocabularyExampleSentence --> VocabularyExampleSentenceId

FlashCardReview --> FlashCardId
FlashCardReview --> UserId
FlashCardReview --> ContentId
FlashCardReview --> FsrsCardState
VocabularyFlashCardData --> FlashCardId
VocabularyFlashCardData *-- "0..*" SentenceData

note right of FlashCardReview
Rendering contract:
- isReversed = false:
  front: vocabulary.surface (German)
  back: vocabulary.translation (English)
  + vocabulary.exampleSentences list (sentence + translation)
- isReversed = true:
  front: vocabulary.translation (English)
  back: vocabulary.surface (German)
  + vocabulary.exampleSentences list (sentence + translation)

Storage rule:
- No vocabulary text/examples are stored in flashcard rows.
- Flashcard aggregate keeps only stable references + FSRS state.
end note

note right of VocabularyFlashCardData
Single domain data flow point for vocabulary cards:
- fetched vocabulary content -> VocabularyFlashCardData -> response view
- no direct adapter-to-response mapping in service flow
end note

note left of FlashCardReview
Module boundaries:
- vocabulary aggregate ownership:
  language_learning_system/domain/vocabulary
- flashcard aggregate ownership:
  flashcards_study/domain/models
- relation is by stable ID reference (contentId), not by embedding.
end note

note bottom of Vocabulary
Vocabulary remains the single source of lexical content.
Flashcards keep references only.
end note

note bottom of FlashCardReview
Private vocabulary cards are generated on vocabulary create/update.
They are fetched via:
GET /api/v1/vocabulary-flashcards/cards/*
end note

@enduml
